article.description: Brittany McPhee and Shannon Coffee scored 13 points apiece and No. 11 Stanford blitzed Wichita State 87-39 on Friday at the Cancun Challenge.
article.headline: No. 11 Stanford women cruise past Shockers 87-39 in Cancun
article.linkText: No. 11 Stanford women cruise past Shockers 87-39 in Cancun
article.story:
RIVERIA MAYA, Mexico --  Brittany McPhee and Shannon Coffee scored 13 points apiece and No. 11 Stanford blitzed Wichita State 87-39 on Friday at the Cancun Challenge.

Erica McCall added 13 points for the Cardinal (5-1) and Alana Smith, Nadia Fingall and Marla Snezek had 11 each.

Stanford scored the last seven points of the first quarter to take a 20-11 lead and then scored the first 16 of the second. The Cardinal made 11 of 13 shots in the second quarter and led 46-15 at the break. They outscored the Shockers (1-4) 22-2 on points in the paint and got 20 points off 13 turnovers

With Smith and McCall grabbing eight rebounds and Coffee seven, Stanford dominated the boards 45-18. The Cardinal ended up at 62 percent shooting (33 of 53) and a 50-13 advantage on inside points.

No player reached double figures for the Shockers, who shot 26 percent (14 of 54). In their only other meeting, the Shockers beat Stanford 71-68 on Dec. 4, 1980.

Stanford wraps up the round-robin tournament facing Purdue on Saturday.
